    <h2>JAMB Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <details>
      <summary>1. Is JAMB required for all tertiary institutions?</summary>
      <p>Yes, most Nigerian universities and polytechnics require JAMB for admission. However, some private institutions and foreign academic programs may offer alternative routes or entrance exams that do not require JAMB.</p>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>2. Can I gain admission without JAMB?</summary>
      <p>Yes, you can gain admission without JAMB through the following options:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>JUPEB (Joint Universities Preliminary Examinations Board)</li>
        <li>IJMB (Interim Joint Matriculation Board)</li>
        <li>Pre-degree or foundation programs</li>
        <li>Some private universities offer Direct Entry admission options</li>
      </ul>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>8. How can I download the JAMB syllabus?</summary>
      <p>To access the JAMB syllabus:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Visit the official JAMB website at <a href="https://www.jamb.gov.ng" target="_blank">https://www.jamb.gov.ng</a> and navigate to the “Syllabus” section.</li>
        <li>Alternatively, search online for “JAMB 2025 Syllabus PDF download” to get access through verified educational platforms.</li>
      </ul>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>9. How many times can I take JAMB?</summary>
      <p>There is no restriction on the number of times you can take the JAMB exam. As long as you meet the eligibility criteria each year, you can register and write JAMB repeatedly.</p>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>10. Can I change my course or institution after JAMB?</summary>
      <p>Yes. After JAMB results are released, candidates are allowed to apply for a Change of Course or Institution through their JAMB profile. This process typically requires a fee (around ₦2,500) and can be done online through the JAMB portal.</p>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>11. What is the minimum score to gain admission?</summary>
      <p>The minimum JAMB score required for admission depends on the institution and the course you're applying for. Generally:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Universities: 160–200+</li>
        <li>Polytechnics: 120–150</li>
        <li>Colleges of Education: 100–120</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Competitive courses like Medicine, Law, and Engineering often require higher scores.</p>
    </details>
